# Component Conventions

## File locations

- Reusable UI primitives → `components/ui/`
- Page sections → `components/sections/`
- Admin editor → `components/admin/`
- Shared config & data → `lib/invitation.ts`
- Server actions → `lib/actions/invitation.ts`
- Class merging → `lib/cn.ts`

## Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — const arrow, typed props, cn() for classes
type ButtonProps = {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
  children: React.ReactNode;
};

const Button = ({ variant = "primary", children }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button className={cn("rounded-full px-6 py-2", variant === "primary" && "bg-rose")}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

- Use `const` arrow functions for components
- Prefix event handlers with `handle` (`handleClick`, `handleKeyDown`)
- Props typed with `type` (not `interface` unless extending)
- Compose classes with `cn()` from `@/lib/cn`
- No business logic in `components/ui/` primitives — keep them presentational
- Page sections receive `data: InvitationData` prop — do not import static config

## Imports

```tsx
import { Button, Card, Container } from "@/components/ui";
import { type InvitationData } from "@/lib/invitation";
```
